Amazon.com is an ecommerce platform that sells many product lines, including media ([[book]]s, movies, music, and software), apparel, baby products, [[consumer electronics]], [[Cosmetics|beauty products]], gourmet food, groceries, health and personal care products, industrial & scientific supplies, kitchen items, [[jewelry]], watches, lawn and garden items, musical instruments, [[Sports equipment|sporting goods]], tools, automotive items, toys and games, and farm [[agrochemical|supplies]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=All Departments |url=https://www.amazon.com/b?ie=UTF8&node=19097677011 |access-date=September 28, 2022 |website=Amazon.com}}</ref> and [[agronomy|consulting services]].<ref name="Rai">{{cite news | access-date=September 20, 2022 | last=Rai | year=2021 | website=[[Bloomberg News]] | url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-09-01/amazon-woos-farmers-to-help-unlock-world-s-no-2-farm-market | title=Amazon Tries to Crack India's Produce Market by Wooing Farmers}}<!--- Bloomberg changed title from Crop-related queries, mobile alerts — Amazon tries to tap India’s agri sector by wooing farmers ---></ref> Amazon websites are country-specific (for example, amazon.com for the U.S. and amazon.fr for France), though some offer international shipping.<ref>{{cite web |title=Amazon.com, Form 10-K, Annual Report, Filing Date Jan 30, 2013 |url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/1562/0001193125-13-028520.pdf |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20221009/http://pdf.secdatabase.com/1562/0001193125-13-028520.pdf |archive-date=October 9, 2022 |url-status=live |access-date=February 26, 2013 |publisher=SEC database}}</ref>

Visits to ''amazon.com'' grew from 615&nbsp;million annual visitors in 2008,<ref>[http://siteanalytics.compete.com/amazon.com/ SnapShot of amazon.com, amazonellers.com, walmart.com] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100516154151/http://siteanalytics.compete.com/amazon.com/ |date=May 16, 2010 }}. Retrieved April 12, 2008.</ref> to more than 2 billion per month in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Web visitor traffic to Amazon.com 2022 |url=https://www.statista.com/statistics/623566/web-visits-to-amazoncom/ |access-date=September 28, 2022 |website=Statista |language=en}}</ref> The ecommerce platform is the 14th most visited website in the world.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Top Websites Ranking |url=https://www.similarweb.com/top-websites/ |access-date=September 28, 2022 |website=[[SimilarWeb]]}}</ref>

Results generated by Amazon's search engine are partly determined by promotional fees.<ref name="New Yorker">{{cite magazine |last=Packer |first=George |author-link=George Packer |date=February 17, 2014 |title=Cheap Words |url=https://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2014/02/17/140217fa_fact_packer?currentPage=all |magazine=[[The New Yorker|newyorker.com]] |access-date=March 22, 2014}}</ref> The company's [[Internationalization and localization|localized]] storefronts, which differ in selection and prices, are differentiated by [[top-level domain]] and [[country code]]:
